113
00:11:11,607 --> 00:11:14,311
'"l ask you, sir, what sort of word is that?

114
00:11:14,902 --> 00:11:17,819
'"lt's 'aoow' and 'garn'
that keep her in her place

115
00:11:18,321 --> 00:11:20,813
'"Not her wretched clothes and dirty face

116
00:11:22,284 --> 00:11:25,569
'"Why can't the English
teach their children how to speak?

117
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:29,203
'"This verbal class distinction
by now should be antique

118
00:11:29,624 --> 00:11:32,874
'"lf you spoke as she does, sir,
instead of the way you do

119
00:11:33,294 --> 00:11:35,785
'"Why, you might be selling flowers, too'"

120
00:11:36,005 --> 00:11:37,036
I beg your pardon.

121
00:11:37,131 --> 00:11:40,465
