About 21 .

1893
02:26:26,913 --> 02:26:29,784
I should say about 5 foot 7.

1894
02:26:31,042 --> 02:26:34,991
Her eyes? Let me think now. Her eyes....

1895
02:26:35,337 --> 02:26:37,081
-Brown.
-Brown.

1896
02:26:39,842 --> 02:26:44,550
Her hair? Good Lord.
Sort of a nondescript neutral sort of--

1897
02:26:44,638 --> 02:26:46,265
Brown, brown, brown!

1898
02:26:46,392 --> 02:26:49,061
You heard what he said?
Brown, brown, brown, yes.

1899
02:26:49,145 --> 02:26:51,636
No. This is her residence. 27A--

1900
02:26:51,730 --> 02:26:55,514
Yes, about between 3:00 and 4:00
this morning, I understand.

1901
02:26:56,694 --> 02:26:59,778
No.... She's no relation, no.

1902
02:27:00,739 --> 02:27:03,656
Well, let's call her a good friend, shall we?

1903
02:27:04,117 --> 02:27:05,577
I beg your pardon?

1904
02:27:05,703 --> 02:27:08,454
Listen to me, I don't like the tenor
of that question.

1905
02:27:08,539 --> 02:27:10,910
What the girl does here is our affair.

1906
02:27:12,208 --> 02:27:15,660
Your affair is to get her back
so she can continue doing it.

1907
02:27:16,296 --> 02:27:17,790
Well, I'm dashed!

1908
02:27:20,342 --> 02:27:23,342
'"What in heaven
could have prompted her to go?

1909
02:27:23,428 --> 02:27:25,587
'"After such a triumph at the ball

1910
02:27:26,431 --> 02:27:27,973
'"What could have depressed her?

1911
02:27:28,058 --> 02:27:32,007
'"What could have possessed her?
I cannot understand the wretch at all'"

1912
02:27:34,188 --> 02:27:38,318
Higgins, I have an old school chum
at the Home Office. Perhaps he could help.

1913
02:27:38,403 --> 02:27:40,229
Think I'll give him a ring.

1914
02:27:41,781 --> 02:27:44,485
Whitehall: 7244, please.

1915
02:27:47,161 --> 02:27:49,830
'"Women are irrational
That's all there is to that

1916
02:27:49,914 --> 02:27:52,583
'"Their heads are full of
Cotton, hay and rags

1917
02:27:53,000 --> 02:27:56,749
'"They're nothing but exasperating
lrritating, vacillating, calculating

1918
02:27:56,837 --> 02:27:59,589
'"Agitating, maddening
And infuriating hags'"

1919
02:28:01,133 --> 02:28:04,299
I want to speak
to Mr. Brewster Budgin, please.

1920
02:28:05,261 --> 02:28:06,673
Yes, I'll wait.

1921
02:28:12,060 --> 02:28:16,105
Pickering, why can't a woman
be more like a man?

1922
02:28:16,982 --> 02:28:18,440
I beg your pardon?

1923
02:28:18,692 --> 02:28:21,977
Yes, why can't a woman
be more like a man?

1924
02:28:22,862 --> 02:28:25,569
'"Men are so honest, so thoroughly square

1925
02:28:25,993 --> 02:28:28,744
'"Eternally noble, historically fair

1926
02:28:29,412 --> 02:28:32,448
'"Who, when you win
Will always give your back a pat?

1927
02:28:32,832 --> 02:28:35,120
'"Why can't a woman be like that?

1928
02:28:36,544 --> 02:28:39,035
'"Why does every one do
What the others do?

1929
02:28:39,964 --> 02:28:42,289
'"Can't a woman learn to use her head?

1930
02:28:43,425 --> 02:28:46,047
'"Why do they do everything
Their mothers do?

1931
02:28:46,262 --> 02:28:49,595
'"Why don't they grow up
Well, like their father instead?

1932
02:28:49,807 --> 02:28:52,298
'"Why can't a woman take after a man?

1933
02:28:52,935 --> 02:28:55,806
'"Men are so pleasant, so easy to please

1934
02:28:56,313 --> 02:28:59,148
'"Whenever you're with them
You're always at ease

1935
02:28:59,650 --> 02:29:02,650
'"Would you be slighted
lf I didn't speak for hours?

1936
02:29:02,819 --> 02:29:05,441
'"Would you be livid
lf I had a drink or two?

1937
02:29:06,156 --> 02:29:09,073
'"Would you be wounded
lf I never sent you flowers?

1938
02:29:09,201 --> 02:29:11,952
'"Well, why can't a woman be like you?

1939
02:29:13,371 --> 02:29:15,699
'"One man in a million may shout a bit

1940
02:29:16,752 --> 02:29:19,422
'"Now and then
There's one with slight defects

1941
02:29:20,131 --> 02:29:22,586
'"One perhaps whose truthfulness
You doubt a bit

1942
02:29:22,675 --> 02:29:26,424
'"But by and large
We are a marvelous sex

1943
02:29:26,721 --> 02:29:29,128
'"Why can't a woman take after a man?

1944
02:29:29,849 --> 02:29:32,683
'"Cause men are so friendly
Good-natured and kind

1945
02:29:33,143 --> 02:29:35,848
'"A better companion
You never will find

1946
02:29:36,605 --> 02:29:39,476
'"lf I were hours late for dinner
Would you bellow?

1947
02:29:39,775 --> 02:29:42,610
'"lf I forgot your silly birthday
Would you fuss?

1948
02:29:42,986 --> 02:29:45,857
'"Would you complain
lf I took out another fellow?

1949
02:29:46,240 --> 02:29:48,944
'"Well, why can't a woman be like us?'"

1950
02:29:52,704 --> 02:29:54,661
Is Mr. Brewster Budgin there?

1951
02:29:55,206 --> 02:29:59,038
Bruzzie, you'll never guess who this is.

1952
02:30:00,837 --> 02:30:04,620
You're quite right, it is. Good heavens.
By George, what a memory.

1953
02:30:05,719 --> 02:30:08,388
How are you, Bruzzie?
Nice to hear your voice.

1954
02:30:09,430 --> 02:30:12,799
What? You don't say.
Has it really been 30 years, Bruzzie?

1955
02:30:13,225 --> 02:30:14,470
Right. Yes, oceans of water.

1956
02:30:14,560 --> 02:30:16,802
Listen, Bruzzie, I'll tell you why I rang up.

1957
02:30:16,896 --> 02:30:20,644
Something rather unpleasant
has happened. Could I come and see you?

1958
02:30:20,733 --> 02:30:22,772
I could, yes. Now, straight away?

1959
02:30:22,860 --> 02:30:24,022
Right. Good. Thank you.

1960
02:30:24,111 --> 02:30:26,519
Goodbye, Bruzzie. Thank you very much.

1961
02:30:33,662 --> 02:30:36,497
Mrs. Pearce, I'm going along
to the Home Office.

1962
02:30:37,207 --> 02:30:39,496
I do hope you find her, Colonel Pickering.

1963
02:30:39,584 --> 02:30:41,376
Mr. Higgins will miss her.

1964
02:30:41,586 --> 02:30:45,205
Mr. Higgins will miss her, eh?
Blast Mr. Higgins, I'll miss her!

1965
02:30:57,145 --> 02:30:59,268
-Mrs. Pearce?
-Yes, sir.

1966
02:30:59,647 --> 02:31:00,643
Where's the Colonel?

1967
02:31:00,732 --> 02:31:02,890
He's gone to the Home Office, sir.

1968
02:31:03,943 --> 02:31:08,901
There you are. I'm disturbed and he runs
for help. Now there's a good fellow.

1969
02:31:10,741 --> 02:31:13,113
Mrs. Pearce, you're a woman.

1970
02:31:14,453 --> 02:31:17,289
'"Why can't a woman be more like a man?

1971
02:31:18,124 --> 02:31:20,959
'"Men are so decent
Such regular chaps

1972
02:31:21,377 --> 02:31:23,998
'"Ready to help you
Through any mishaps

1973
02:31:24,629 --> 02:31:27,203
'"Ready to buck you up
Whenever you are glum

1974
02:31:27,800 --> 02:31:30,469
'"Why can't a woman be a chum?

1975
02:31:31,720 --> 02:31:34,211
'"Why is thinking
Something women never do?

1976
02:31:35,141 --> 02:31:37,596
'"And why is logic never even tried?

1977
02:31:38,352 --> 02:31:41,186
'"Straightening up their hair
ls all they ever do

1978
02:31:41,396 --> 02:31:44,847
'"Why don't they straighten up
The mess that's inside?

1979
02:31:44,941 --> 02:31:47,517
'"Why can't a woman behave like a man?

1980
02:31:48,238 --> 02:31:50,811
'"lf I was a woman
Who'd been to a ball

1981
02:31:51,491 --> 02:31:54,160
'"Been hailed as a princess
By one and by all

1982
02:31:54,827 --> 02:31:57,745
'"Would I start weeping
Like a bathtub overflowing?

1983
02:31:57,914 --> 02:32:00,487
'"Or carry on as if my home were in a tree?

1984
02:32:01,042 --> 02:32:04,042
'"Would I run off
And never tell me where I'm going?

1985
02:32:04,295 --> 02:32:07,000
'"Why can't a woman be like me?'"

1986
02:32:11,343 --> 02:32:14,427
You mean that after you'd done
this wonderful thing for them...

1987
02:32:14,513 --> 02:32:16,008
...without making a mistake...

1988
02:32:16,099 --> 02:32:18,091
...they just sat there
and never said a word?

1989
02:32:18,184 --> 02:32:21,967
Never petted you, or admired you,
or told you how splendid you'd been?

1990
02:32:22,062 --> 02:32:22,726
Not a word.

1991
02:32:22,813 --> 02:32:26,017
They just congratulated each other
on how marvelous they'd been.

1992
02:32:26,108 --> 02:32:28,599
The next moment, how glad they were
it was all over...

1993
02:32:28,694 --> 02:32:30,485
...and what a bore it had all been.

1994
02:32:30,570 --> 02:32:33,820
This is appalling. I should not
have thrown my slippers at him.

1995
02:32:33,907 --> 02:32:36,151
I should have thrown the fire irons.

1996
02:32:36,287 --> 02:32:37,449
Who's that?

1997
02:32:37,579 --> 02:32:40,284
Henry. I knew it wouldn't be too long.

1998
02:32:41,875 --> 02:32:43,250
Now, remember...

1999
02:32:44,002 --> 02:32:48,331
...you not only danced with a prince
last night, you behaved like a princess.

2000
02:32:55,222 --> 02:32:57,926
Mother, the most confounded thing....
Do you--

2001
02:33:01,477 --> 02:33:02,390
You!

2002
02:33:03,229 --> 02:33:06,349
Good afternoon, Professor Higgins.
Are you quite well?

2003
02:33:07,817 --> 02:33:11,944
Of course you are. You are never ill.
Would you care for some tea?

2004
02:33:12,738 --> 02:33:15,609
Don't you dare try that game on me.
I taught it to you.

2005
02:33:15,700 --> 02:33:17,443
Get up, come home and stop being a fool.

2006
02:33:17,535 --> 02:33:19,077
You've caused me enough trouble.

2007
02:33:19,161 --> 02:33:23,158
Very nicely put indeed, Henry.
No woman could resist such an invitation.

2008
02:33:23,248 --> 02:33:24,825
How did this baggage get here?

2009
02:33:24,919 --> 02:33:27,873
Eliza came to see me this morning
and I was delighted to have her.

2010
02:33:27,963 --> 02:33:30,917
If you don't promise to behave yourself
I'll ask you to leave.

2011
02:33:31,008 --> 02:33:33,000
I'm to put on my Sunday manners
for this...

2012
02:33:33,093 --> 02:33:36,877
...thing that I created out of the squashed
cabbage leaves of Covent Garden?

2013
02:33:36,972 --> 02:33:38,715
That's precisely what I mean.

2014
02:33:38,807 --> 02:33:40,385
I'll see her damned first.

2015
02:33:40,475 --> 02:33:43,595
However did you learn good manners
with my son around?

2016
02:33:43,811 --> 02:33:48,141
It was very difficult. I should never have
known how ladies and gentlemen behave...

2017
02:33:48,233 --> 02:33:50,854
...if it hadn't been for Colonel Pickering.

2018
02:33:52,278 --> 02:33:54,520
He showed me that he felt
and thought about me...

2019
02:33:54,613 --> 02:33:57,983
...as if I were something better
than a common flower girl.

2020
02:34:00,620 --> 02:34:04,202
You see, Mrs. Higgins,
apart from the things one can pick up...

2021
02:34:04,373 --> 02:34:08,122
...the difference between a lady
and a flower girl isn't how she behaves...

2022
02:34:08,211 --> 02:34:10,002
...but how she is treated.

2023
02:34:12,799 --> 02:34:15,293
I'll always be a flower girl
to Professor Higgins...

2024
02:34:15,387 --> 02:34:19,005
...because he always treats me
as a flower girl and always will.

2025
02:34:19,725 --> 02:34:21,847
I'll always be a lady to Colonel Pickering...

2026
02:34:21,935 --> 02:34:25,221
...because he always treats me
as a lady and always will.

2027
02:34:30,109 --> 02:34:31,568
Henry, don't grind your teeth.

2028
02:34:31,652 --> 02:34:34,487
The bishop is here.
Shall I show him into the garden?

2029
02:34:34,572 --> 02:34:37,063
The bishop and the professor?
Good heavens, no!

2030
02:34:37,158 --> 02:34:38,985
I should be excommunicated.

2031
02:34:39,285 --> 02:34:41,194
I'll see him in the library.

2032
02:34:41,954 --> 02:34:44,623
Eliza, if my son starts breaking up things...

2033
02:34:44,833 --> 02:34:47,537
...l give you full permission
to have him evicted.

2034
02:34:47,627 --> 02:34:51,838
Henry, I suggest you stick to two subjects:
the weather and your health.

2035
02:35:19,659 --> 02:35:21,699
You've had a bit of your own back,
as you say.

2036
02:35:21,786 --> 02:35:25,203
Have you had enough and will you
be reasonable or do you want any more?

2037
02:35:25,290 --> 02:35:27,283
You want me back to pick up
your slippers...

2038
02:35:27,375 --> 02:35:30,411
...and put up with your tempers
and fetch and carry for you.

2039
02:35:30,503 --> 02:35:32,294
I didn't say I wanted you back at all.

2040
02:35:32,380 --> 02:35:33,755
Then what are we talking about?

2041
02:35:33,839 --> 02:35:35,465
Well, about you, not about me.

2042
02:35:35,550 --> 02:35:38,254
If you come back you'll be treated
as you always have.

2043
02:35:38,344 --> 02:35:40,586
I can't change my nature or my manners.

2044
02:35:40,680 --> 02:35:43,514
My manners are exactly
the same as Colonel Pickering's.

2045
02:35:43,599 --> 02:35:47,383
That's not true. He treats a flower girl
as if she were a duchess.

2046
02:35:47,520 --> 02:35:49,761
I treat a duchess
as if she was a flower girl.

2047
02:35:49,855 --> 02:35:52,013
I see. The same to everybody.

2048
02:35:52,482 --> 02:35:55,237
The great secret is not a question
of good manners...

2049
02:35:55,321 --> 02:35:58,772
...or bad manners
or any particular sort of manner...

2050
02:35:59,283 --> 02:36:02,651
...but having the same manner
for all human souls.

2051
02:36:04,537 --> 02:36:06,946
The question is not
whether I treat you rudely...

2052
02:36:07,041 --> 02:36:10,456
...but whether you've ever heard me
treat anyone else better.

2053
02:36:10,544 --> 02:36:12,501
I don't care how you treat me.

2054
02:36:12,587 --> 02:36:15,672
I don't mind your swearing at me.
I shouldn't mind a black eye.

2055
02:36:15,757 --> 02:36:18,841
I've had one before this.
But I won't be passed over!

2056
02:36:19,052 --> 02:36:20,926
Get out of my way,
for I won't stop for you.

2057
02:36:21,012 --> 02:36:23,135
You talk about me as though
I was a motorbus.

2058
02:36:23,222 --> 02:36:27,434
So you are a motorbus. All bounce and go
and no consideration for anybody.

2059
02:36:27,685 --> 02:36:30,437
But I can get along without you.
Don't you think I can't!

2060
02:36:30,521 --> 02:36:32,929
I know you can. I told you, you could.

2061
02:36:36,361 --> 02:36:38,934
You've never wondered, I suppose,
whether...

2062
02:36:39,030 --> 02:36:41,567
...whether I could get along without you?

2063
02:36:42,658 --> 02:36:45,697
Don't you try to get around me.
You'll have to.

2064
02:36:46,914 --> 02:36:49,535
So I can, without you or any soul on earth.

2065
02:36:52,669 --> 02:36:56,881
I shall miss you, Eliza. I've learned
something from your idiotic notions.

2066
02:36:57,550 --> 02:37:00,087
I confess that humbly and gratefully.

2067
02:37:03,054 --> 02:37:05,427
Well, you have my voice
on your gramophone.

2068
02:37:05,516 --> 02:37:10,011
When you feel lonely without me you can
turn it on. It has no feelings to hurt.

2069
02:37:11,521 --> 02:37:14,272
Well, I can't turn your soul on.

2070
02:37:16,943 --> 02:37:19,185
You are a devil!

2071
02:37:20,155 --> 02:37:22,645
You can twist the heart in a girl
just as easily...

2072
02:37:22,740 --> 02:37:25,196
...as some can twist her arms to hurt her.

2073
02:37:25,285 --> 02:37:27,112
What am I to come back for?

2074
02:37:27,453 --> 02:37:29,529
For the fun of it. That's why I took you on.

2075
02:37:29,622 --> 02:37:32,373
You may throw me out tomorrow
if I don't do everything you want.

2076
02:37:32,458 --> 02:37:35,876
Yes. And you may walk out tomorrow
if I don't do everything you want.

2077
02:37:35,964 --> 02:37:37,162
And live with my father?

2078
02:37:37,257 --> 02:37:39,794
Yes, or sell flowers.
Would you rather marry Pickering?

2079
02:37:39,884 --> 02:37:43,632
I wouldn't marry you if you asked me
and you're nearer my age then what he is.

2080
02:37:43,721 --> 02:37:46,924
-Than he is.
-I'll talk as I like, you're not my teacher.

2081
02:37:47,016 --> 02:37:49,851
That's not what I want
and don't you think it is.

2082
02:37:49,935 --> 02:37:52,177
I've always had chaps enough
wanting me that way.

2083
02:37:52,271 --> 02:37:55,356
Freddy Hill writes me twice
and three times a day. Sheets and sheets.

2084
02:37:55,441 --> 02:37:59,390
In short, you want me to be
as infatuated about you as he is, is that it?

2085
02:37:59,486 --> 02:38:03,483
No, I don't. That's not the sort of feeling
I want from you.

2086
02:38:04,575 --> 02:38:06,318
I want a little kindness.

2087
02:38:06,743 --> 02:38:10,444
I know I'm a common, ignorant girl,
and you're a book-learned gentleman...

2088
02:38:10,538 --> 02:38:12,780
...but I'm not dirt under your feet.

2089
02:38:13,041 --> 02:38:18,035
What I done...what I did was not
for the taxis and the dresses...

2090
02:38:18,463 --> 02:38:22,128
...but because we were pleasant together
and I come to...came...

2091
02:38:23,467 --> 02:38:24,964
...to care for you.

2092
02:38:25,263 --> 02:38:27,055
Not to want you to make love to me...

2093
02:38:27,140 --> 02:38:30,224
...and not forgetting the difference
between us, but...

2094
02:38:30,309 --> 02:38:31,969
...more friendly like.

2095
02:38:34,188 --> 02:38:36,430
Well, of course. That's how I feel.

2096
02:38:37,066 --> 02:38:40,649
And how Pickering feels.
Eliza, you're a fool!

2097
02:38:40,736 --> 02:38:42,111
That's not the proper answer.

2098
02:38:42,196 --> 02:38:44,153
It's the only answer
till you stop being an idiot.

2099
02:38:44,239 --> 02:38:46,398
To be a lady, you must stop
feeling neglected...

2100
02:38:46,492 --> 02:38:49,113
...if men don't spend half their time
sniveling over you...

2101
02:38:49,203 --> 02:38:51,242
...and the other half giving you black eyes.

2102
02:38:51,330 --> 02:38:53,737
You find me cold, unfeeling, selfish,
don't you?

2103
02:38:53,832 --> 02:38:55,909
Off with you to the sort of people you like.

2104
02:38:56,001 --> 02:38:57,910
Marry a sentimental hog
with lots of money...

2105
02:38:58,003 --> 02:39:00,754
...and thick lips to kiss you,
and thick boots to kick you.

2106
02:39:00,839 --> 02:39:04,006
If you can't appreciate what you have,
then get what you can appreciate.

2107
02:39:04,344 --> 02:39:07,179
I can't talk to you.
You always turn everything against me.

2108
02:39:07,263 --> 02:39:08,971
I'm always in the wrong.

2109
02:39:09,181 --> 02:39:11,423
Don't be too sure you have me
under your feet...

2110
02:39:11,517 --> 02:39:13,639
...to be trampled on and talked down.

2111
02:39:13,727 --> 02:39:17,264
I'll marry Freddy, I will,
as soon as I'm able to support him.

2112
02:39:18,734 --> 02:39:21,355
The poor devil who couldn't get a job
as an errand boy...

2113
02:39:21,445 --> 02:39:23,402
...even if he had the guts to try?

2114
02:39:23,489 --> 02:39:27,238
Don't you understand?
I have made you a consort for a king!

2115
02:39:27,410 --> 02:39:30,363
Freddy loves me.
That makes him king enough for me.

2116
02:39:30,454 --> 02:39:33,454
I don't want him to work.
He wasn't brought up to do it as I was.

2117
02:39:33,540 --> 02:39:35,284
I'll go and be a teacher.

2118
02:39:35,709 --> 02:39:37,702
What'll you teach, in heaven's name?

2119
02:39:37,795 --> 02:39:40,332
What you taught me. I'll teach phonetics.

2120
02:39:44,718 --> 02:39:48,965
I'll offer myself as an assistant
to that brilliant Hungarian.

2121
02:39:49,848 --> 02:39:53,512
What, that imposter? That humbug?
That toadying ignoramus?

2122
02:39:53,893 --> 02:39:56,052
Teach him my methods, my discoveries?

2123
02:39:56,146 --> 02:39:58,767
You take one step in that direction,
I'll wring your neck!

2124
02:39:58,856 --> 02:40:02,307
Wring away! What do I care?
I knew you'd strike me one day.

2125
02:40:05,574 --> 02:40:08,527
That's done you, 'Enry 'lggins, it 'as.

2126
02:40:08,618 --> 02:40:11,702
Now, I don't care for your bullyin'
an' your big talk.

2127
02:40:12,997 --> 02:40:14,871
'"What a fool I was

2128
02:40:14,958 --> 02:40:16,582
'"What a dominated fool

2129
02:40:16,876 --> 02:40:19,663
'"To think you were the earth and sky

2130
02:40:20,254 --> 02:40:21,962
'"What a fool I was

2131
02:40:22,047 --> 02:40:23,755
'"What an addle-pated fool

2132
02:40:23,924 --> 02:40:27,340
'"What a mutton-headed dolt was I

2133
02:40:28,512 --> 02:40:31,762
'"No, my reverberating friend

2134
02:40:32,224 --> 02:40:36,352
'"You are not the beginning and the end'"

2135
02:40:39,106 --> 02:40:40,600
You impudent hussy!

2136
02:40:40,815 --> 02:40:45,359
There's not an idea in your head or a word
in your mouth that I haven't put there.

2137
02:40:46,863 --> 02:40:51,441
'"There'll be spring every year without you

2138
02:40:52,285 --> 02:40:55,490
'"England still will be here without you

2139
02:40:56,208 --> 02:40:59,908
'"There'll be fruit on the tree
And a shore by the sea

2140
02:41:00,003 --> 02:41:03,205
'"There'll be crumpets and tea without you

2141
02:41:03,798 --> 02:41:06,965
'"Art and music will thrive without you

2142
02:41:07,635 --> 02:41:10,801
'"Somehow Keats will survive without you

2143
02:41:11,472 --> 02:41:15,256
'"And there still will be rain
On that plain down in Spain

2144
02:41:15,351 --> 02:41:18,554
'"Even that will remain without you

2145
02:41:19,146 --> 02:41:20,889
'"l can do...

2146
02:41:22,816 --> 02:41:24,276
'"...without you

2147
02:41:25,486 --> 02:41:28,237
'"You, dear friend

2148
02:41:28,322 --> 02:41:31,525
'"Who talk so well

2149
02:41:32,826 --> 02:41:36,326
'"You can go to

2150
02:41:36,538 --> 02:41:39,207
'"Hartford, Hereford and Hampshire

2151
02:41:39,874 --> 02:41:42,828
'"They can still rule the land without you

2152
02:41:43,503 --> 02:41:46,755
'"Windsor Castle will stand without you

2153
02:41:47,301 --> 02:41:50,918
'"And without much ado
We can all muddle through

2154
02:41:51,012 --> 02:41:52,803
'"Without you! '"

2155
02:41:53,014 --> 02:41:54,758
You brazen hussy!

2156
02:41:55,475 --> 02:41:59,175
'"Without your pulling it the tide comes in

2157
02:41:59,771 --> 02:42:03,684
'"Without your twirling it the earth can spin

2158
02:42:03,857 --> 02:42:08,354
'"Without your pushing them
the clouds roll by

2159
02:42:09,155 --> 02:42:14,280
'"lf they can do without you, Ducky,
So can I

2160
02:42:14,535 --> 02:42:18,034
'"l shall not feel alone without you

2161
02:42:18,289 --> 02:42:21,491
'"l can stand on my own without you

2162
02:42:22,042 --> 02:42:25,826
'"So go back in your shell
I can do bloody well--'"

2163
02:42:26,380 --> 02:42:30,163
'"By George, I really did it
I did it, I did it

2164
02:42:30,342 --> 02:42:33,011
'"l said I'd make a woman and indeed I did

2165
02:42:33,178 --> 02:42:35,885
'"l knew that I could do it
I knew it, I knew it

2166
02:42:36,058 --> 02:42:38,596
'"l said I'd make a woman
and succeed I did'"

2167
02:42:38,977 --> 02:42:40,768
Eliza, you're magnificent.

2168
02:42:41,146 --> 02:42:43,636
Five minutes ago you were
a millstone around my neck...

2169
02:42:43,731 --> 02:42:45,772
...and now you're a tower of strength.

2170
02:42:45,859 --> 02:42:47,483
A consort battleship.

2171
02:42:48,862 --> 02:42:50,439
I like you this way.

2172
02:42:52,698 --> 02:42:56,531
Goodbye, Professor Higgins.
You shall not be seeing me again.

2173
02:43:10,174 --> 02:43:11,205
Mother!

2174
02:43:14,512 --> 02:43:16,753
What is it, Henry? What's happened?

2175
02:43:18,557 --> 02:43:19,720
She's gone.

2176
02:43:19,850 --> 02:43:22,423
Well, of course, dear.
What did you expect?

2177
02:43:25,900 --> 02:43:27,098
What am I to do?

2178
02:43:27,193 --> 02:43:28,817
Do without, I suppose.

2179
02:43:30,570 --> 02:43:32,314
And so I shall.

2180
02:43:35,576 --> 02:43:38,576
If the Higgins' oxygen burns up
her little lungs...

2181
02:43:38,703 --> 02:43:41,455
...let her seek some stuffiness
that suits her.

2182
02:43:42,248 --> 02:43:45,748
She's an owl sickened
by a few days of my sunshine.

2183
02:43:46,128 --> 02:43:48,120
Let her go. I can do without her.

2184
02:43:48,213 --> 02:43:50,668
I can do without anyone.
I have my own soul!

2185
02:43:50,757 --> 02:43:53,591
My own spark of divine fire!

2186
02:43:57,806 --> 02:43:59,135
Bravo, Eliza.

2187
02:44:19,579 --> 02:44:22,745
'"Damn, damn, damn, damn

2188
02:44:25,085 --> 02:44:27,243
'"l've grown accustomed to her face

2189
02:44:31,048 --> 02:44:33,088
'"She almost makes the day begin

2190
02:44:34,219 --> 02:44:37,552
'"l've grown accustomed to the tune
That she whistles night and noon

2191
02:44:37,638 --> 02:44:41,387
'"Her smiles, her frowns
Her ups, her downs

2192
02:44:41,517 --> 02:44:43,426
'"Are second nature to me now

2193
02:44:44,687 --> 02:44:46,929
'"Like breathing out and breathing in

2194
02:44:48,065 --> 02:44:51,434
'"l was serenely independent and content
Before we met

2195
02:44:52,027 --> 02:44:54,982
'"Surely I could always be that way again

2196
02:44:57,157 --> 02:45:00,857
'"And yet I've grown
Accustomed to her looks

2197
02:45:01,828 --> 02:45:03,536
'"Accustomed to her voice

2198
02:45:04,166 --> 02:45:07,914
'"Accustomed to her face'"

2199
02:45:22,725 --> 02:45:23,971
Marry Freddy.

2200
02:45:24,644 --> 02:45:28,724
What an infantile idea. What a heartless,
wicked, brainless thing to do.

2201
02:45:29,482 --> 02:45:32,186
But she'll regret it. She'll regret it.

2202
02:45:32,693 --> 02:45:35,363
It's doomed before they even take the vow!

2203
02:45:37,031 --> 02:45:40,696
'"l can see her now
Mrs. Freddy Eynsford-Hill

2204
02:45:40,868 --> 02:45:43,359
'"ln a wretched little flat above a store

2205
02:45:43,997 --> 02:45:46,867
'"l can see her now, not a penny in the till

2206
02:45:46,957 --> 02:45:49,495
'"And a bill collector beating at the door

2207
02:45:50,043 --> 02:45:52,712
'"She'll try to teach the things I taught her

2208
02:45:52,963 --> 02:45:55,172
'"And end up selling flowers instead

2209
02:45:56,010 --> 02:45:58,086
'"Begging for her bread and water

2210
02:45:58,512 --> 02:46:01,216
'"While her husband has
his breakfast in bed

2211
02:46:04,810 --> 02:46:09,270
'"ln a year or so
when she's prematurely gray

2212
02:46:09,356 --> 02:46:12,226
'"And the blossom in her cheek
has turned to chalk

2213
02:46:13,026 --> 02:46:16,229
'"She'll come home and lo
he'll have upped and run away

2214
02:46:16,363 --> 02:46:19,233
'"With a social-climbing heiress
from New York

2215
02:46:19,491 --> 02:46:20,771
'"Poor Eliza

2216
02:46:20,867 --> 02:46:22,491
'"How simply frightful

2217
02:46:22,577 --> 02:46:24,202
'"How humiliating

2218
02:46:24,913 --> 02:46:26,407
'"How delightful

2219
02:46:29,250 --> 02:46:32,120
'"How poignant it will be
On that inevitable night

2220
02:46:32,294 --> 02:46:35,000
'"When she hammers on my door
ln tears and rags

2221
02:46:35,506 --> 02:46:38,590
'"Miserable and lonely
Repentant and contrite

2222
02:46:39,426 --> 02:46:41,917
'"Will I take her in
Or hurl her to the wolves?

2223
02:46:42,012 --> 02:46:44,885
'"Give her kindness
Or the treatment she deserves?

2224
02:46:45,268 --> 02:46:48,471
'"Will I take her back
Or throw the baggage out?

2225
02:46:51,440 --> 02:46:53,480
'"Well, I'm a most forgiving man

2226
02:46:54,277 --> 02:46:56,814
'"The sort who never could, ever would

2227
02:46:57,279 --> 02:47:00,399
'"Take a position
and staunchly never budge

2228
02:47:04,036 --> 02:47:05,744
'"A most forgiving man

2229
02:47:08,999 --> 02:47:11,038
'"But I shall never take her back

2230
02:47:12,168 --> 02:47:14,327
'"lf she were crawling on her knees

2231
02:47:14,921 --> 02:47:17,542
'"Let her promise to atone
Let her shiver, let her moan

2232
02:47:17,632 --> 02:47:21,297
'"l'll slam the door
And let the hellcat freeze'"

2233
02:47:24,431 --> 02:47:26,055
Marry Freddy.

2234
02:47:40,948 --> 02:47:43,154
'"But I'm so used to hear her say

2235
02:47:44,035 --> 02:47:45,778
'"'Good morning' every day

2236
02:47:46,579 --> 02:47:48,536
'"Her joys, her woes

2237
02:47:49,206 --> 02:47:51,779
'"Her highs, her lows

2238
02:47:52,000 --> 02:47:53,994
'"Are second nature to me now

2239
02:47:55,963 --> 02:47:58,204
'"Like breathing out and breathing in

2240
02:48:00,050 --> 02:48:03,633
'"l'm very grateful she's a woman
And so easy to forget

2241
02:48:04,638 --> 02:48:07,971
'"Rather like a habit one can always break

2242
02:48:10,727 --> 02:48:14,725
'"And yet I've grown
Accustomed to the trace

2243
02:48:15,732 --> 02:48:18,270
'"Of something in the air

2244
02:48:19,736 --> 02:48:24,281
'"Accustomed to her face'"

2245
02:50:01,922 --> 02:50:06,919
Oh, we are proud. He ain't above
givin' lessons, not 'im. I 'eard 'im say so.

2246
02:50:07,597 --> 02:50:09,719
I ain't come here to ask
for any compliment...

2247
02:50:09,807 --> 02:50:12,843
...and if my money's not good enough,
I can go elsewhere.

2248
02:50:12,935 --> 02:50:14,216
Good enough for what?

2249
02:50:14,312 --> 02:50:16,933
Good enough for you.
Now you know, don't ya?

2250
02:50:17,106 --> 02:50:19,513
I'm come to 'ave lessons.
And to pay for 'em, too...

2251
02:50:19,608 --> 02:50:20,639
...make no mistake.

2252
02:50:20,734 --> 02:50:22,477
What do you want, my girl?

2253
02:50:22,569 --> 02:50:25,939
I want to be a lady in a flow'r shop,
'stead o' sellin'...

2254
02:50:26,073 --> 02:50:28,480
...at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.

2255
02:50:28,575 --> 02:50:33,071
But they won't take me unless I can talk
more genteel. He said he could teach me.

2256
02:50:33,789 --> 02:50:38,783
Well, 'ere I am ready to pay. Not askin'
any favor, and he treats me as if I was dirt.

2257
02:50:39,586 --> 02:50:43,335
I know what lessons cost as well as you do
and I'm ready to pay.

2258
02:50:43,966 --> 02:50:47,132
I won't give more than a shillin'.
Take it or leave it.

2259
02:50:47,469 --> 02:50:51,466
It's almost irresistible.
She's so deliciously low.

2260
02:50:52,264 --> 02:50:54,840
So horribly dirty. I'll take it.

2261
02:50:55,562 --> 02:50:58,728
I'll make a duchess
of this draggle-tailed guttersnipe.

2262
02:51:00,566 --> 02:51:03,402
I washed my face and 'ands
before I come, I did.

2263
02:51:18,000 --> 02:51:20,076
Where the devil are my slippers?